<div class="block">
<h3>Tutorial</h3>
<ol>
<li>See the editing field</li>
<p>&emsp;To make the editing field visible, just tap your back navigation once.</p>
<li>See the menu</li>
<p>&emsp;There are two ways to see the menu, but they are not same in list. First is by clicking the back navigation of your mobile phone while the editing field is active, and the other one is long press the gray line separator</p>
<li>Can I customized the editing field?</li>
<p>&emsp;Yes, you can. By going to the menu, look for the Settings, and you may edit the editing field by what you want.</p>
<li>How to use external syntax?</li>
<p>&emsp;Just like using the normal syntax of <code>&lt;link href="style" rel="stylesheet"&gt; and &lt;script="script.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;b</code>. But now, make it easier than the last version. I make it auto saved thru the default folder project.</p>
<li>Where is the JavaScript Console?</li>
<p>&emsp;You may see the JavaScript console by holding the line separator of the app.</p>
</ol>
</div>
